@@yHISTORY@@W

The Sentinel tradition descends from the Jackal Tribunal's sentence enforcers
— practitioners who carried out verdicts through disciplined physical
intervention rather than priestly magic. When the Solar Court collapsed, the
Tribunal's intellectual methods were absorbed by the Cleric tradition and its
militant remnants devolved into the Jackal Synod. But the sentence enforcers
preserved a third path: the Tribunal's embodied practice of reading subjects,
applying measured restraining force, and ending confrontations through precise
physical action informed by deep observation.

@@ySENTINEL@@W

Sentinels are WIS-based melee combatants who fight through perceptive judgment
rather than raw power. Their combat methodology descends from the Tribunal's
core competency: reading multiple signals (posture, breath, weapon angle,
footing) and synthesizing them into a predictive model of the opponent's intent.

@@yPassive class abilities@@W
  * @@wTestimonial Guard@@W (level 12): WIS-scaled resistance to fear, charm,
    and mental effects. At 5+ testimony marks, immunity to fear.
  * @@wMeasured Response@@W (level 30): chance to counter-attack after a
    successful parry or dodge. Generates testimony on proc.

@@yUnique Sentinel mechanics@@W
  * Prime mortal attribute is @@wWisdom@@W.
  * @@wTestimony@@W: marks accumulated on a single target through successful
    defensive reading (dodge, parry, block). See @@mhelp testimony@@W.
  * @@wVerdict@@W: spend testimony marks for a single devastating strike whose
    damage and debuff scale with marks. See @@mhelp verdict@@W.
  * Best against tough, durable targets — the Sentinel's power increases the
    longer they fight the same opponent.
  * 6 HP / 1 Mana per level — medium durability, survives through avoidance.

